fields.customfield_10312: After I reply once and I'm not logged in, my information is stored for 1 day.
fields.description: As a buyer, if I'm not logged in, I would still like the browser to retain my name, email, and phone number after I have replied once. This can help me respond quicker in the future. The duration of the cookie can be very short: one session or one day. See examples on www.gumtree.co.za. See ULIVZ-36609. Currently it's set to 1 day.

comments.body: This doesn't include code change in RUI or work in new development page..

Why do we need to consider RUI here? I thought the scope is only for MX. May be I'm mistaken on something? 

Tagging [~jerome] - when you work on new development page, can you please also implement?

The prototype of storing sensitive data is in branch ULIVZ-37687-encrypt-data. We can work based on that. How to use this API can be seen in description of https://github.corp.ebay.com/ecg-global/bolt-2dot0-frontend/pull/1164
Reopen it as deploy PP failed, should fix deploy PP issue
